{
  "texts": [
    "Here, (CNN) serves as the feature extractor, while (LSTM) takes charge of classification, as illustrated in Fig. 7.",
    "The model parameters and architecture commence with a convolutional layer comprising 128 filters, featuring a kernel size of 8, along with L2 and bias regularizers set at 0.002276.",
    "A max-pooling layer and a dropout layer with a rate of 0.2 follow this.",
    "Subsequently, an (LSTM) layer with 256 units is employed, succeeded by a flattened layer.",
    "Two dense layers are added, each with 525 units and ReLU activation, complemented by a dropout rate of 0.2."
  ]
}